Please consider donations for Ovarian Cancer research in my mother Deborah Prutting’s name. 🕊️
This cancer usually affects women middle aged and older and commonly shows up at a late stage. Currently there is not a proven path for a cure. Mom battled this cancer for 33 months with a warrior mindset and lived full of grace until the very end. She passed on 8/8/23 but is forever in spirit and left an indelible mark on this world. Love all the way ❣️
A celebration of her life / memorial is being planned for 9/23 at our family farm in New Canaan CT. A link to her obituary will be added to my bio. Thank you 🙏
RIP “Debbie Dynamo” god bless you 🪽 ❤️ ♾️

Who’s that girl!? Happy 7th birthday Layla! What can I say about my favorite human? Well let’s just say my love for you is like a super power, blessed with the gift of being your daddy. Let’s keep the good times rolling kid ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️ 11/06/23 🪄

For my daughter’s 7th bday I wanted to gift her something other than what she might expect. So I commissioned artist @andrea_selby to live paint Layla’s Mermaid 🧜‍♀️ themed birthday party at @chelseapiersct water park. I think the result is really beautiful and hopefully will be something she cherishes as she grows. I am a patron of the arts, thanks to my parents, (especially my late mother @debprutting — who always had me and my sister @lizpmen in front of an easel growing up - she passed that love of art on to both her grandkids as well, for which I’m so grateful 🙏) therefor i am very happy to support a talented artist any chance I get. My daughter is an artist herself, but she is like a living art piece to me. I am truly enamored by her and will always be. I love you Layla. Love you so much. Keep dreaming big, believing in yourself, trusting in god, and living your “Love Story”. 🩷🩵 - Daddy 11/06/23
